generate an SSH key and copy it to each app server's sudo user account.

# 1. Generate a key (if one doesn't already exist)
ssh-keygen -t rsa -N "" -f ~/.ssh/id_rsa

# 2. Copy the public key to each app server
ssh-copy-id <to all the servers required>

# 3. Verify password-less access
ssh to all the servers


If `ssh-copy-id` is not available in the environment, use:

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh tony@stapp01 "mkdir -p ~/.ssh && chmod 700 ~/.ssh && cat >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys && chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys"

repeat the above for all the servers
